# Data comes in different shapes and forms. Computers treat different types of data in different ways.
# You know that a variable is storing a string when it is surrounded by quotation marks.
# String is the data type for a piece of text. The qoutation marks tell the computer that a value needs to be stored as a string.
# Integers are whole numbers without a decimal point. They can be positive, negative or zero.
# Float is the data type for numbers with decimal places, they can be positive or negative.
# Concatenation is when you use the + addition operator with string values the two strings are joined together.
# Anything in quotation marks will be treated as a string, even numbers.
# You won't be able to do math operatinos if numbers are surrounded by quotes. They will be treated as strings.